<item>
            <title>[LU-17532] Don&apos;t LASSERT on received data</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17532</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a server receives corrupted data from a bad client, this could trigger an LASSERT (for instance in server_bulk_callback) and lead to the crash of the server.&lt;br/&gt;
However, it is possible to manage such errors in a softer way that does not end with a server failure.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
